title.children: Australia fighting hard with the bat after being sent in on day one at Old Trafford

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well it looked good live and it looked even better from an English point of view on replay. He got across to the off side, got hit in line with off stump and it was going on to hit middle. Smith goes for 41 off 52 and that's a big wicket for England.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: OUT! SMITH IS OUT LBW!

children.content: Well it looked good live and it looked even better from an English point of view on replay.
He got across to the off side, got hit in line with off stump and it was going on to hit middle.
Smith goes for 41 off 52 and that's a big wicket for England.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Plenty of action in that session, with both openers falling, but more than 100 runs scored in just 25 overs. Steve Smith is 33 off 34. Marnus Labuschagne has been more circumspect for 29 off 60. Neither of these batters would be happy with their series thus far and there's been plenty of talk about it in the long break between Tests. They look locked in, but both have made starts and thrown it away by gifting their wickets to England, so they need to stay locked in after lunch.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: Australia 2-107 (Labuschagne 29, Smith 33)
